Server:

```bash
target/release/nullifier-pir serve \
  --snapshot-path data/nullifiers.bin \
  --backend local-ipir \
  --host 127.0.0.1 \
  --port 8090 \
  --setup-seed 7
```

The server was rebuilt after adding the `simplepir-kernel` default
`ChunkedSplitKernel` path and after adding the `/query` response timing header
`x-nullifier-pir-server-time-us`.

Sample 1:

```bash
/usr/bin/time -f 'process_wall_s=%e' target/release/nullifier-pir query \
  --server-url "http://127.0.0.1:8090" \
  --snapshot-path "data/nullifiers.bin" \
  --nullifier-hex "b3cdb97715d5e3dd624fc87906b9d13b4e4ec6a63989d989936f2504f0a1f706" \
  --setup-seed 7
```

